original: The Retching Netch
string: 呕吐气母

original: So this is the fabled College of Winterhold. Amazing.
string: 看来这就是传说中的冬堡学院了，太神奇了。

original: I hope we don't bump into any Forsworn around here. I heard they're as wild as a pack of beasts.
string: 希望我们不会在这儿遇到弃誓者。听说他们和野兽没什么两样。

original: The Pale reminds me of the northern part of Solstheim... rife with freezing cold weather and full of unfriendly creatures.
string: 苍原让我想到了索瑟海姆的北部……天气寒冷且到处都是有敌意的生物。

original: I can't believe how carelessly the dead are buried here. I can't imagine my body just rotting away like that.
string: 不敢相信死者就这样敷衍地埋在这儿了，我的尸体要是那样腐烂下去简直不敢想。

original: Whiterun... the pride of Skyrim. Doesn't look like much to me. Now Blacklight on the other hand, that's a proper city.
string: 白漫城……天际的骄傲。在我看来不太像啊。不过另一方面，说明黑光城才是大城市。

original: I lived in the Gray Quarter of Windhelm for years... it's a wretched place full of bitter Dunmer. Let's be done here quickly.
string: 我在风舵城的灰民区住过一段时间……那里有很多愤恨不平的丹莫，是个可悲之地。我们完事儿了就赶紧走吧。

original: Can you imagine what Markarth must have looked like when the dwarves were living here? I can't even begin to imagine.
string: 你能想象矮人们还在时的马卡斯是什么样吗？我是想不出来。

original: Solitude... home to the East Empire Company, the heartless bastards.
string: 独孤城……东帝国公司的老巢，那些心狠手辣的混蛋。

original: So this is Riften. Glover Mallory told me a good deal about the place. It looks exactly as I'd pictured.
string: 原来这就是裂谷城。葛洛文·马洛里跟我说过这儿的很多事情。和我想象的一模一样。

original: You may want to be careful down here... the Thieves Guild makes the Ratway its home.
string: 这里可要小心点儿......盗贼公会把鼠道当成了家。

original: Dawnstar is full of struggling miners. Sounds a lot like a certain town in Solstheim, eh?
string: 晨星城满是些在生死线上挣扎的矿工。听上去就像索瑟海姆的某个镇子，是吧？

original: Ugh, what a wretched place. Who would build a town in the middle of a swamp?
string: 啊，这地方太糟糕了。谁会把镇子建在沼泽中央啊？

original: Riverwood looks peaceful. If I had to settle in Skyrim, this might be the place I'd choose.
string: 河木镇看起来很安宁。如果我要在天际安家，可能会选在这儿。

original: Vampires are wretched beings. Feeding off others the way they do... it's disgusting.
string: 吸血鬼是可恶的生物。他们靠吸食他人为生......真让人恶心。

original: Warlocks practice all sorts of foul sorcery. We should proceed with caution.
string: 这些术士啥邪术都会。我们推进时务必小心。

original: Careful, it looks like something's lived here recently.
string: 注意，这儿最近好像有什么生物住过。

original: Damn bandits are worse than the vermin that infest the ash wastes back home.
string: 该死的强盗简直比老家那些灰烬里肆虐的害虫还可恶。

original: Dragons, eh? Good, I was looking for a challenge.
string: 龙，是吧？很好，我正在找些挑战呢。

original: There are restless dead about... I suggest we proceed with caution.
string: 附近有未安息的亡灵……我建议谨慎行事。

original: Despite the foul beings that infest this place, I'm certain we'll find plenty of wealth to make it worth our time.
string: 尽管这地方被些恶心玩意儿污染了，我很确定能找到大笔财富，绝不会浪费我们的时间。

original: The dwarves were a clever race. I wonder what happened to them?
string: 矮人以前是个很聪明的种族。我好奇他们到底遇到了什么事？

original: To think the Falmer are loosely related to the Dunmer sends shivers down my spine.
string: 想到伐莫是丹莫的远亲真让我全身发毛。

original: Not much of a farm. How do they expect to grow anything in this ash-free soil?
string: 这农场真不像样。他们怎么在无灰土里种出作物来？

original: The Forsworn are little more than beasts. They won't listen to reason, so prepare for the worst.
string: 弃誓者不过是野兽罢了。他们蛮不讲理，所以做好最坏的打算吧。

original: Ugh, the stench. We must be nearing a giant's home.
string: 呃啊，这股臭味。我们肯定离巨人的窝不远了。

original: Becoming a hagraven requires a sacrifice to their foul deity. Show them no mercy before we become one of the victims.
string: 成为乌鸦鬼婆需要向他们的邪神献祭。面对他们不要手软，不然我们就成牺牲品了。

original: I never fancied becoming a miner... didn't want to spend the rest of my days cracking rocks.
string: 我从没想过当个矿工……我不想把一辈子花在敲打石头上。

original: I was briefly in the employ of an Orc warrior once. I had to quit because he refused to bathe. Disgusting.
string: 我曾短暂为一名兽人战士效力过。我只好辞职，因为他拒绝洗澡。真恶心。

original: Nice place you have here. I never knew you were so wealthy.
string: 你这边还不赖嘛，我都没想到你这么有钱。

original: I wonder how many souls were lost when this ship met its fate.
string: 不知道这艘船沉的时候有多少冤魂丧生了。

original: Spriggan are loathsome creatures. They summon some of the most benign beings of the forest and bend them to their will.
string: 木灵真是令人生恶，它们会召唤森林中最温顺的动物，让它们屈服于自己的意志。

original: What would possess someone to give their allegiance to Hircine, only to see their free will taken from them like this?
string: 是什么让一个人效忠海尔辛，只为了看着自由意志像这样被剥夺？

original: Anytime you want to head for Skyrim, I'm right with you. I've spent enough time on Solstheim to last a lifetime.
string: 等你想回天际了，我也陪你。我在索瑟海姆都快过一辈子了。

original: Hope we don't run into too many ash spawn out here.
string: 但愿我们在这儿别碰上太多灰烬怪。

original: I'm not sure why House Redoran is so insistent on maintaining Solstheim. Seems like more trouble than it's worth.
string: 我不确定为什么瑞多然家这么坚持要控制索瑟海姆，这里的麻烦看来比利益要大。

original: With the ash from Red Mountain covering half the island, it's astonishing how much Solstheim reminds me of home.
string: 红山的火山灰都盖住半个岛了，真没想到索瑟海姆让我想起了故乡。

original: How can the Skaal stand it up here? It's freezing!
string: 斯卡尔人怎么能忍受这个地方？冷死了！

original: The Telvanni are amazing. Look what they've grown from the ash... have you ever seen anything like it?
string: 泰瓦尼很神奇，看看他们从灰烬里种出了什么……你见过这种东西吗？

original: I've called Raven Rock my home for a number of years. Azura knows why... it's a mess.
string: 我已经把鸦石镇当自己的家很多年了，天晓得为什么……太糟了。

original: Seems like things are looking up in Raven Rock now that the mine's open. It's a nice change.
string: 看来矿场开张后事态有所好转，是个不错的转变。

original: I'm glad that I'm finally traveling with someone who seems competent. My last patron was killed trying to tackle an entire fort of bandits alone.
string: 很高兴终于能和一个过得去的人旅行，上个雇主死于坚持要单挑一整座堡垒的强盗。

original: I grew up in the city of Blacklight in Morrowind. If you ever get the chance, you should visit there... it's spectacular.
string: 我在晨风的黑光城长大，你要是有机会该去看看……非常壮观。

original: I don't know why I decided to make my way to Solstheim to seek my fortune. I should have stayed at home.
string: 我不懂自己为什么要来索瑟海姆寻求财运。我本该待在家里。

original: You like my chitin armor? It was specially crafted for me by Grendis Rolovo... one of the finest master armorsmiths in Morrowind.
string: 你喜欢我的甲壳护甲吗？是格兰蒂斯·若洛夫专门帮我打造的……他是晨风最好的护甲锻造师之一。

original: All this walking... I wish there was a silt strider around here.
string: 走了这么久……真希望这附近有泥沙漫步者。

original: I wonder what became of Saint Jiub? I met him once, you know.
string: 我想知道圣鸠步怎么样了？我见过他一面，知道吧。

original: Our journey's been quite rewarding so far. Hopefully, you won't mind sharing the spoils.
string: 我们的旅途收获颇丰。希望你不会介意分享战利品。

original: You look quite ill. Perhaps a visit to a shrine is in order?
string: 你看起来病恹恹的。或许是时候去一趟祭坛了？

original: Did you take my Chitin armor? Wait, what you're wearing, it looks suspiciously like mine.
string: 你拿了我的甲壳护甲吗？等等，你穿的这身......看起来像我的。

original: Do you know what happened to my Chitin armor? That was made for me specially you know, by Grendis Rolovo. I feel lost without it.
string: 你知道我的甲壳护甲去哪儿了吗？那件是格兰蒂斯·若洛夫专门为我打造的。没有它我感到失落。

original: What was that? The ale's gone bad? Did they just say the ale's gone bad? But I just had some.
string: 什么？啤酒坏了？他们说啤酒坏了？可我刚刚还喝过。

original: Goodness. This woman never shuts up, does she?
string: 天啊。这个女人就没停过话吗？

original: I really hope Frea knows what she's doing, eh?
string: 我真的很希望芙瑞雅知道自己在做什么，对吧？

original: Let's not stay here longer than we need to.
string: 我们不要在这里待太久。

original: Eh?
string: 嗯？

original: We should keep our wits about us in here. Who knows what hidden dangers there are.
string: 这里我们要保持警惕。谁知道有什么隐藏的危险。

original: This place makes me uneasy. Stay on guard.
string: 这个地方让我感到不安。保持警戒。

original: I really, really don't like this place.
string: 我真的、真的不喜欢这个地方。

original: Seeing this place, you can see why the Dragons razed Miraak's temple to the ground.
string: 看看这个地方，你就知道为什么龙族会将米拉克的神殿夷为平地了。

original: Search round the creepy rooms. Sure, what fun.
string: 在阴森的房间里搜索吧。当然，这很有趣。

original: Did I mention I don't like this place?
string: 我提过我不喜欢这个地方吗？

original: In places like this, I'm always on guard.
string: 在这样的地方，我总是保持警戒。

original: I'd really like to get out of here.
string: 我真的很想离开这里。

original: Come on, get up. What are you even doing down there?
string: 快起来，你在下面干什么呢？

original: I'm not feeling so good. Let me... just... recover a little.
string: 我感觉不太好。让我...休息一会儿...

original: This fight is not going very well is it?
string: 这场战斗进行得并不顺利，是吧？

original: I'm a bit low on magicka. Give me a little time to get it back up.
string: 我的魔力有点低。给我一点时间恢复一下。

original: I wish I could say it's good to be back in Windhelm, but it really isn't.
string: 我真希望能说回到风舵是件好事，但事实并非如此。

original: It's pretty dull here isn't it?
string: 这里真的很无聊，不是吗？

original: First time I've been to Rorikstead, but I read about it in Atlas of Dragons. There was a dragon buried here according to that.
string: 我第一次来到洛利克镇，但《巨龙图志》里提到过它。据书上说，这里曾经埋葬过一条龙。

original: Passed through Riverwood a few times with my former employer, it's nice and quiet here, I like it.
string: 我曾经和以前的雇主多次路过河木镇，这里很安静，我喜欢这种氛围。

original: There's a few people here that Glover Mallory told me about that I think I'd like to have a talk with.
string: 这里有几个人是葛洛文·马洛里告诉我要见的人，我想和他们聊聊。

original: I don't think I've been here before. But it's so dull, I probably wouldn't have remembered anyway.
string: 我从没来过这里吧。不过这地方太无聊了，我可能也记不住。

original: This place is a bit boring, or so I've heard.
string: 听说这个地方有点无聊。

original: You know I've heard about that bridge but I've never seen it up close. It's quite impressive.
string: 我听说过那座桥，但从没近距离看过。确实很壮观。

original: This snow's no better than the ash. I hope we don't have to stay here long.
string: 这雪和灰烬没什么两样。我希望我们不会在这里待太久。

original: It's not bad here. Bit warmer than most places in Skyrim.
string: 这里还不错。比天际大部分地方暖和多了。

original: I'd heard a lot about Markarth. But honestly? It's not that impressive.
string: 我听说过很多关于马卡斯的事。说实话？并不那么让人惊叹。

original: This is my first time back in Whiterun since the unfortunate incident with my former patron. Quite sad when I think about it.
string: 自从和以前的委托人发生那件不幸的事后，我第一次回到白漫。想起来还真让人伤感。

original: Oh this is lovely. If you like foggy swamps.
string: 哇，这地方真美。如果你喜欢雾气弥漫的沼泽的话。

original: Got to admit, Solitude's an impressive city. But I've heard things about its residents that aren't quite so impressive.
string: 不得不承认，独孤是座雄伟的城市。但我听说当地居民的传闻，可不那么让人敬佩。

original: Try blocking this!
string: 试试挡住这个！

original: Die!
string: 去死吧！

original: Feel my sword!
string: 感受我的剑锋！

original: Ouch! That actually hurt!
string: 哎哟！那一下真的很痛！

original: That was a lucky blow!
string: 运气不错，这一剑刺中了！

original: You'll regret that!
string: 你会后悔的！

original: Ha! I've had more painful kitchen accidents!
string: 哈！我还经历过更痛的厨房意外呢！

original: I'll admit, you hit harder than most Nords!
string: 我得承认，你的拳头比大多数诺德人还要重！

original: Ow! That wolf just bit me.
string: 哎哟！那头狼咬了我一口。

original: That Skeever bit me. I hope I don't catch something nasty.
string: 那只恶鼠咬了我。我可不想染上什么恶疾。

original: Stop shedding dust on me!
string: 别把灰尘弄到我身上！

original: I'm being assaulted by a bag of bones. Glorious!
string: 我正被一具骨头袋子攻击。太荣耀了！

original: Keep your cursed hands off me!
string: 别用你那该死的手碰我！

original: That stings! And now you made me angry!
string: 该死！你还让我生气了！

original: Oh! That's going to leave a scar.
string: 哦！那可要留下疤了。

original: Damn, hit me with an arrow!
string: 该死，你用箭射我！

original: Ha! That dagger barely left a mark!
string: 哈！那把匕首几乎没留下伤痕！

original: Ouch. Bolts can really hurt.
string: 哎哟。弩箭真的很痛！

original: Damn, that axe is sharp!
string: 该死，那把斧子真锋利！

original: The best swordsman in all of Morrowind, and you have me fighting skeevers?
string: 晨风最好的剑客，却让我和恶鼠战斗？

original: Dwarven technology, still trying to kill us centuries later. Quite remarkable.
string: 矮人科技，数百年后还想杀了我们。真了不起。

original: Argh! Mechanical spiders are worse than actual spiders!
string: 该死！机械蜘蛛比真蜘蛛还可恶！

original: Back to your tomb, corpse!
string: 回你的坟墓去吧，死尸！

original: You should have stayed dead!
string: 你本该就该死在哪里！

original: Let's see how well your bones hold up against a proper blade!
string: 让我看看你的骨头在真正的刀刃下能撑多久！

original: Get back in your hole!
string: 滚回你的洞里去！

original: Crawl back into your tunnels, wretch!
string: 爬回你的地道里去，可怜虫！

original: Come on then! Let's see what you're made of!
string: 来吧！让我看看你是用什么做的！

original: Come on, let's see if you can actually hit me!
string: 来吧，让我看看你是否真的能打中我！

original: Come on bandit! Make me earn my pay!
string: 来吧，强盗！让我看看你是否值得我拿这份钱！

original: I'll make you wish you'd stayed in your coffin!
string: 我会让你后悔没待在棺材里！

original: Don't stand in front of the mouth! That's lesson one.
string: 别站在我的刀口前！这是第一课。

original: Oh good, another idiot volunteering to die today.
string: 哦，好，又有一个自愿送死的白痴。

original: Try not to bleed on my armor. It's hard enough to clean as it is.
string: 尽量别把血溅到我的盔甲上。本来就够难清洗了。

original: You really think you can take me? I admire the optimism. The stupidity, less so!
string: 你真的以为自己能打得过我？我佩服你的乐观精神。但愚蠢就不那么让人欣赏了！

original: You people have the worst recruitment strategy I've ever seen.
string: 你们的招募策略真的是我见过最差的。

original: Just what we needed...
string: 这正是我们所需要的......

original: Try not to get shot by that archer.
string: 小心别被那个弓箭手射中。

original: Watch out for the crossbow!
string: 当心弩！

original: Get the one with the crossbow before he gets you!
string: 先干掉那个用弩的家伙，别让他先对付你！

original: That puny little butter knife - is it meant to be fearsome?
string: 那把小小的奶油刀——你是想让它看起来可怕吗？

original: So you've got a big sword. Am I supposed to be scared?
string: 你有一把大剑？我应该害怕吗？

original: You think you can best me in a sword fight? Me?
string: 你以为你能在剑术上战胜我？我？

original: The size of your sword doesn't matter, it's how you use it.
string: 你的剑有多大并不重要，重要的是你如何使用它。

original: You come at me with a dagger? How amusing. Anyway, you get to die next!
string: 你拿着匕首就敢来挑战我？真有趣。不管怎么说，你下一个就要去见阎王了！

original: Come on, see if you can hit me with that axe!
string: 来吧，看看你能不能用那把斧头砍中我！

original: An axe versus a sword? How quaint!
string: 斧头对阵剑？真可爱！

original: Malacath would laugh at your prowess in battle!
string: 玛拉凯斯会对你的战斗技巧嗤之以鼻！

original: I've bested so many Orcs, I've lost count!
string: 我击败过那么多兽人，都数不清了！

original: Come on Orc, see if you can hit me with your big sword!
string: 来吧，兽人，看看你能不能用你那把大剑砍中我！

original: You'll soon be as dead as your empire!
string: 你很快就会和你的帝国一样，一命呜呼！

original: You fight like a tax collector!
string: 你战斗起来像个税吏一样！

original: You think you can take me in a sword fight?
string: 你以为你能在剑斗中战胜我？

original: Was that a war cry, or a hiccup?
string: 那算是战吼还是打嗝？

original: You should have stayed on your farm, Nord!
string: 你本该待在你的农场里，诺德人！

original: Your ancestors would be embarrassed!
string: 你的祖先都会为你感到羞耻！

original: That axe would be better suited to chopping wood!
string: 那把斧头更适合砍柴！

original: Come on half-blood, let's see what you've got!
string: 来吧，混血儿，让我看看你有什么本事！

original: Your spells won't save you now, Breton!
string: 你的法术救不了你，布莱顿人！

original: Oh are you going to stab me with your little knife?
string: 哦，你要用你那把小刀刺我吗？

original: Arrogant fool! You've not much time left in this world!
string: 狂妄的傻瓜！你在这个世界剩下的时间不多了！

original: The only thing superior about you is your ability to bleed!
string: 你唯一优秀的地方就是你会流血！

original: You won't be so clever when I take your head!
string: 你等着，我要砍下你的脑袋！

original: Call yourself a swordsman?
string: 你也敢自称剑士？

original: Back to your forest, little elf!
string: 回你的森林去，小精灵！

original: Your Pact won't save you now!
string: 你的契约现在救不了你！

original: Come on little Bosmer, see if you can hit me with that bow!
string: 来吧，小波斯莫，看看你那把弓能不能碰到我！

original: This one picked the wrong person to mess with!
string: 这个家伙找错人惹事了！

original: I'm going to cut off your tail and slap you with it!
string: 我要砍下你的尾巴，再用它抽你！

original: Look who brought an axe to a sword fight!
string: 看看谁拿斧头来送死！

original: Come on Argonian, let's dance!
string: 来吧，阿尔贡，我们跳个舞！

original: I'll send you back to the mud Argonian!
string: 我要把你送回泥沼，阿尔贡！

original: Should have stayed in your swamp!
string: 本该待在你的沼泽里！

original: You're a disgrace to Morrowind!
string: 你是晨风的耻辱！

original: I expected better from one of my own!
string: 我对你的期望可比这高多了！

original: A crossbow? Who do you think you are, Dawnguard?
string: 弩？你当自己是谁啊，黎明守卫？

original: Aren't you supposed to be a fearsome warrior?
string: 你不是什么可怕的战士吗？

original: I'll put you back in the desert!
string: 我要把你送回沙漠！

original: Come on, I thought your kind were good with the sword!
string: 算了吧，我还以为你这类人剑法还行呢！

original: Come on, Thalmor scum!
string: 算了吧，梭默垃圾！

original: Not today Thalmor. Not today!
string: 今天不是你的日子，梭默！今天不是！

original: That frost will kill you. Don't stand still!
string: 那冰霜会要了你命，别站着不动！

original: That cold will kill you faster than his fists. MOVE!!
string: 那场寒冷会比他的拳头更快地要了你的命。快动起来！！

original: If you're going to shout, now would be an excellent time!
string: 如果你要用龙吼，现在正是时候！

original: Have you met that odd Hlaallu woman? She likes hanging round the House of the Dead. That's just weird.
string: 你见过那个奇怪的女人吗？她总爱在亡者之厅附近晃悠。真让人毛骨悚然。

original: Have you noticed more people talking about mudcrabs and goblins recently?
string: 最近你有没有注意到更多人在讨论泥沼蟹和哥布林？

original: I say, have you heard about that chap that just walks round saying 'I don't know you and I don't care to know you'?
string: 喂，你听说过那个家伙吗？他总是四处走动，说什么‘我不认识你，也不想认识你’？

original: Watch out for that crazy Argonian running around without any shoes on. She's just weird.
string: 小心那个疯狂的阿尔贡，光着脚四处乱跑。她真让人摸不着头脑。

original: Gal bursten it? What does that even mean?
string: ‘Gal bursten’是什么意思？那是什么玩意儿？

original: Have you met that Devaion Redrith fellow? Got an eye for a bargain, that one. Yes, I mean he's tight with his coin.
string: 你见过那个Devaion Redrith家伙吗？那人精于算计，绝不多花一个铜板。是的，我指的就是他。

original: If you see that Shamgob chap round the markets, best stay out of his way eh? Mean looking one that, even for an orc.
string: 如果你在集市上看到那个Shamgob家伙，最好绕道走。那家伙看起来凶神恶煞，就连是个兽人都不例外。

original: I met Niranwil a few days ago in a shop, forget which one. Snooty one, but not bad to look at.
string: 几天前我在一家店里见到了Niranwil，忘记是哪家了。那人挺傲慢的，但长相还算可以。

original: For a Redguard you know, Malandra's not that bad. Easy on the eye at least.
string: 对于你了解的红卫人来说，马兰德拉其实还不错。至少长得还算讨喜。

original: I had a brief conversation with Pelugius Pallidilius not long ago. What a snob. He never stops going on about wine.
string: 不久前我和佩卢吉乌斯·帕利迪利乌斯聊了几句。真够装腔作势的，他总是絮絮叨叨地说什么葡萄酒。

original: Ingjete seems nice. I might try and get her drunk and... you know?
string: 英杰特看起来挺不错的。我或许可以试试让她喝醉......你懂的。

original: Ingarte's a fine looking woman but I simply can't stand the way she talks.
string: 英加特长得很漂亮，但她讲话的方式让我实在受不了。

original: I'd like to buy Fironet a drink sometime. As long as she doesn't sing.
string: 我倒是想请菲罗内特喝一杯。只要她别唱歌就行。

original: Word is if you want to know the latest gossip, speak to Veralene.
string: 听说要想打听最新的八卦，找维拉琳就对了。

original: Watch out for K'vald while we're here. He'll steal your gold if you're not watchful.
string: 我们在这里时，小心点儿瓦尔德。他要是不注意的话，会偷你的金子。

original: Eldawyn only seems interested in wine. But it's not a bad hobby, I suppose.
string: 埃尔达温看起来只对葡萄酒感兴趣。不过，这也算是个不错的爱好吧。

original: That Peragorn, you know, the Bosmer? He seems infatuated with Haelga.
string: 那个佩拉戈恩，也就是那位波斯莫，看起来对哈尔嘉着迷呢。

original: While we're in Riften, watch out for that Khajiit flower seller. She's up to no good if you ask me.
string: 我们在裂谷时，小心那个卖花的卡吉特。依我看，她不怀好意。

original: I met Caylene once on my travels. She puts on quite the one-woman show.
string: 我曾在旅途中遇见过凯琳。她可真会表演一场独角戏。

original: Don't make any deals with that Cassock fellow. He's bad news. Trust me.
string: 别和那个教士卡索克做任何交易。他是个坏人。相信我。

original: Is it just me, or does Nainda follow us about?
string: 是我一个人这么觉得吗？还是奈恩达总是跟着我们？

original: Oh, I wonder if Ongbarn will ever say something actually funny.
string: 我倒想看看翁巴恩什么时候能说出点真正有趣的话。

original: Ongbarn gets about doesn't he? He's in practically every inn we visit.
string: 翁巴恩可真会到处跑。我们去的每家客栈他都会出现。

original: Hiddeke seems to have taken a shine to me. I keep bumping into her.
string: 希德克似乎对我的印象不错。我总是不小心撞见她。

original: Harik's a brute of a man. Best stay on his good side, eh?
string: 哈里克是个彪悍的汉子。最好别惹他生气，对吧？

original: Tavandra is extremely beautiful, but her voice puts even me off.
string: 塔万德拉长得极其美丽，但她的声音连我也受不了。

original: Denlos keeps asking me about what books I've read. What a fool.
string: 登洛斯总问我读过什么书。真够傻的。

original: Thojof is a handsome man. I bet he gets all the ladies chasing after him.
string: 索乔夫是个英俊的男子。我打赌他身后总有女士追随。

original: That Jobeus seems like a clever chap, eh?
string: 乔比乌斯看起来是个聪明人，对吧？

original: Fjotsel is an amazing looking woman. I bet she could teach me a thing or two.
string: 菲约塞尔长得真漂亮。我猜她能教我一两招。

original: That Kazenji seems to be depressed all the time. Poor chap.
string: 卡泽尼看起来总是闷闷不乐。可怜的家伙。

original: Solamar the Pickled? What an odd name. Oh, it's because he's always drinking.
string: 索拉玛尔·皮克尔德？什么奇怪的名字。哦，因为他总是喝酒。

original: Helvenya is just my type you know? Female... and breathing.
string: 海尔文雅正是我喜欢的类型，你知道吗？女性......而且还活着。

original: I'm not keen on that Vitariao fellow. Far too handsome.
string: 我可不喜欢维塔里奥那个家伙。太帅了。

original: Avrenna's a bit of an old bat isn't she?
string: 阿夫雷娜有点老巫婆了，不是吗？

original: Elrereth isn't bad looking, I wouldn't say no.
string: 埃尔雷斯长得还行，我不会说不。

original: I don't usually like Nords that much, but that Aegda's quite the looker.
string: 我平时不太喜欢诺德人，但艾格达长得还不错。

original: I had a drinking match with Adzir once. He drank me under the table.
string: 我曾和阿兹尔喝酒比试过。他把我喝趴下了。

original: Have you seen Vigdid? She's hideous. Even I wouldn't touch her.
string: 你见过维吉迪吗？她长得丑得要命。就连我也不想碰她。

original: Bendywyr seems like he's hiding some dark secret to me.
string: 本迪维尔看起来好像在隐藏什么见不得人的秘密。

original: Why are these idiots talking about mudcrabs all the time?
string: 这些白痴为什么老是絮絮叨叨说泥沼蟹的事？

original: Is it just me or are all inns full of inane chatter these days?
string: 是不是只有我觉着最近旅店里全是些无聊的闲聊？

original: That Jed's an odd fellow isn't he? And don't get me started on his 'jokes'.
string: 杰德这个人有点古怪吧？别提他那些‘笑话’了。

original: Watch yourself around Jed. He's got shifty eyes.
string: 小心点儿杰德，他那双眼睛总是鬼鬼祟祟的。

original: I don't know how Jed gets away with doing nothing all day.
string: 我真不知道杰德是怎么混一天的。

original: I don't really like jokes, but that Chico fellow raises the odd smirk
string: 我本来不喜欢笑话，但奇科那家伙偶尔也能逗出一两声微笑。

original: Can't help but like Chico can you? He's very... infectious.
string: 忍不住就喜欢上奇科了吧？他很... 有感染力。

original: Chico will be doing his routine soon, we should stick around.
string: 奇科快要开始表演了，我们应该留下来看看。

original: Rondelbert looks odd. Talks funny too.
string: 隆德尔伯特看起来很奇怪。说话也怪怪的。

original: Gorthe the Craven eh? Who would call themselves Craven?
string: 戈斯·胆小鬼是吧？谁会给自己取这么个名字？

original: If that jester blows his horn in my face, I'll shove it up his arse.
string: 要是那个小丑在我的脸前吹号，我就把它塞进他屁眼里。

original: That Jonzo fellow does an impression of me. I have to admit, it's pretty good.
string: 那个乔佐家伙模仿我。我得承认，他做得还挺像的。

original: I don't like Calion wots-his-face. Did you hear what he said about me?
string: 我不喜欢卡利恩·什么来着。你听过他怎么说我的吗？

original: The jester that works here. He's just not funny is he?
string: 这里的那个小丑。他压根就不搞笑不是吗？

original: Estelline's a feisty one eh? Do you know if she's... uh... available?
string: 艾斯泰琳可真有脾气，是吧？你知不知道她......呃......是否......有空？

original: I hear Skyrim is full of jesters these days. Nothing like that where I'm from.
string: 我听说最近天际多了不少小丑。我老家可没有这种事。

original: Not the first time I've been in a place like this. Probably not the last either.
string: 我可不是第一次来这种地方了。以后也不会是最后一次。

original: Most that end up in here deserve it. Don't get caught, eh?
string: 进这里来的大多数人都是自找的。别让自己也落得个这样的下场，对吧？

original: I had a stint as a jailor once. All I did was get fat. Like the guards here I bet.
string: 我以前当过监狱看守。结果就胖成这样了。跟这里的卫兵肯定一样。

original: Smell that? I smell the blood... of cattle. And I don't mean animals.
string: 闻到这味道了吗？我闻到的是......牛血。可不是什么动物。

original: Of course it's vampires. It's always vampires.
string: 当然是吸血鬼了。总是吸血鬼。

original: Vampires have no place in this world. We should kill them without remorse.
string: 吸血鬼不该存在于这个世界。我们应该无情地消灭它们。

original: He-he...have you ever, uh, you know? With a Spriggan? Uh. Never mind, forget I asked.
string: 嘿嘿......你有没有、呃、你知道的吗？跟木灵？呃，算了，别管我了。

original: You know, many years ago, I met a Hagraven that was very friendly. Very friendly indeed. In fact I think she had a little crush on me. Can't say I didn't consider it either, I was in a bit of a... dry spell... if you know what I'm getting at.
string: 你知道吗，很多年前我遇到一只非常友好的乌鸦鬼婆。非常友好，真的。实际上，我怀疑她有点喜欢我。我也不否认自己有点考虑过，我当时有点......口干舌燥......如果你明白我的意思。

original: Quite cosy in here. Better than some of the more well known places.
string: 这里挺温馨的。比一些更出名的地方好多了。

original: Well it's never boring with you is it? You bring me to some interesting watering holes.
string: 跟你在一起可从来不无聊是吧？你总是带我去一些有趣的酒馆。

original: Seems a bit off the beaten track here. I wonder if they serve Sujamma or Vintage Brandy?
string: 这里有点偏僻。不知道他们有没有卖苏贾玛或者陈年白兰地？

original: I'm not really a fan of mingling with others in a drinking establishment, but I'll tolerate it.
string: 我本来不太喜欢在酒馆里和别人混在一起，但这次我可以忍一忍。

original: Well, while we're here, we may as well partake of what's on offer, eh?
string: 既然我们都在这里，不如享用一下这里的美味吧？

original: One good thing I like about places like this, there's usually a woman I can - er - never mind.
string: 我喜欢这种地方的一点是，总能找到一个女人——呃——算了，不说也罢。

original: I hope nobody starts a brawl in here. Brawling is just so tedious.
string: 希望这里不会有人打起来。打架可真让人头疼。

original: Do you think they ever get tired of dying in groups?
string: 你觉得他们是否会厌倦成群结队地死去？

original: Another Nord ruin. Let me guess, draugr behind every corner?
string: 又是一处诺德古迹。让我猜猜，每个角落都有尸鬼吗？

original: You'd think after a few centuries they'd learn to stay dead.
string: 你以为几个世纪后他们就会学会待在坟墓里不起来了。

original: (coughing) Oh. Do excuse me. All this dust in here is not good for me.
string: （咳嗽） 噢，抱歉。这里的灰尘可不适合我。

original: Draugr ahead, no doubt. If one of them mutters in Dragon Tongue, brace yourself.
string: 前面肯定有尸鬼。如果有尸鬼用龙语低语，你可要做好准备。

original: Ah, nothing like ancient death traps to brighten the day. Still, better than spending the day in a Nord tavern, I suppose.
string: 古老的死亡陷阱总能让人精神一振。不过，总比整天待在诺德酒馆里好多了。

original: You know, the Dwemer had brilliant minds, but absolutely no idea about interior decorating.
string: 锻莫确实聪明绝顶，但装修品味却差得离谱。

original: If you hear a clanking sound, it's probably NOT your imagination.
string: 如果你听到叮当声，那很可能不是你的想象。

original: I'll stay close, in case you want to get punted into the sky. I hear it's quite the view.
string: 我会待在附近，万一你想被踢上天呢。听说那景色可真美。

original: Orcs and their strongholds. If the forge smoke doesn't kill you, dinner probably will.
string: 兽人和他们的要塞。如果锻铁的烟雾没要你的命，那么晚餐可能会。

original: Spriggans. Lovely to look at, until they rip you apart. Like most women I know.
string: 木灵。看起来很可爱，直到它们把你撕成碎片。跟我认识的大多数女人一样。

original: Never been a fan of cities. Too many people. Too much noise. I prefer somewhere... quieter.
string: 我从来就不喜欢城市。人太多，噪音太大。我更喜欢一些......安静的地方。

original: Bah! These Forsworn remind me of the filth that plagued Blacklight for centuries. Preying on the innocent, farmers and villages slain for plunder.
string: 呸！这些弃誓者让我想起黑光城几个世纪以来的污秽。他们欺压无辜，屠杀农民和村庄，只为掠夺。

original: Let's not pick too many fights with Forsworn, eh? They're fearsome warriors.
string: 我们可别跟弃誓者惹太多事，对吧？他们都是可怕的战士。

original: Every time I slay a bandit, I think of my former patron and how I'm exacting revenge on his killers.
string: 每次我杀死一个强盗，我就会想起我的前任委托人，以及我如何向他的凶手复仇。

original: Only good bandit is a dead one, if you ask me. And let me tell you, my body count is very high.
string: 如果你问我的话，唯一好的强盗就是死强盗。让我告诉你，我的杀戮数量可不低。

original: You bring me to the most charming places. If you find old bones and rotting corpses charming, of course. Which I don't. Obviously.
string: 你总是带我去最迷人的地方。当然，如果你认为腐烂的骨头和尸体很迷人的话。我可不这么认为。显然。

original: You know, I've killed a lot of people in my all years. I wouldn't be surprised if some of them ended up right here.
string: 你知道吗，我这一辈子杀了不少人。要是他们中有人死后真的来到这里，我也不会感到惊讶。

original: Let's just do what we came to do and get out, eh?
string: 我们还是快点完成任务然后离开吧？

original: You should keep your wits about you in here. Never know what's hiding in the shadows.
string: 这里你可得保持警惕。鬼知道黑暗中藏着什么。

original: I sense danger in here. Good job you've got me to watch your arse.
string: 我感受到这里有危险。幸好有我在照顾你的屁股。

original: Not much of a farm. How do they expect to grow anything in this ash-free soil?
string: 这农场真不像样。他们怎么在无灰土里种出作物来？

original: You know, I can say with quite some authority, it's very true what they say about farmer's wives. Aah... that one, sweet summer.
string: 我可以很权威地告诉你，关于农民妻子的那些说法确实不假。唉......那个，甜蜜的夏季。

original: Farmers are a bit stupid if you ask me. You steal their stuff and they pay you to give it back? I mean... what?
string: 农民们有点傻，你说是吧？你偷了他们的东西，他们还付钱让你还给他们？这算什么？

original: I've faced a few Dragon Priests in my time. I'm in no rush to do so again.
string: 我这一辈子遇到过几个龙祭司。我可不想再遇上一次。

original: I'd rather not hang about here too long. I feel a familiar presence. One that disturbs me.
string: 我可不想在这里待太久。我感受到一种熟悉的气息，让我感到不安。

original: You have to watch these little runts. Not much of a threat on their own, but in packs, they can bring down even a seasoned warrior.
string: 你可得小心这些小家伙。单个没什么威胁，但成群结队的话，连老练的战士都能拖下马。

original: Hehe... little green goblins with spears. Charming. Reminds me of some of my former lovers.
string: 嘿嘿......手持长矛的小哥布林。真迷人。让我想起了我昔日的某些情人。

original: Cold, damp, and miserable. Just like my last winter in Morrowind.
string: 寒冷、潮湿，又让人难受。跟我在晨风的上一个冬天一样。

original: Ah, another cave. How exciting. What do you think, bandits or spiders this time?
string: 又是一个山洞？真让人兴奋。这次会是强盗还是蜘蛛呢？

original: An ice cave? Really? This cold wreaks havoc with my old bones. Are we going to be here long?
string: 冰洞？真的？这鬼天气让我的老骨头都受不了。我们要在这里待很久吗？

original: It's freezing in here. My teeth are chattering.
string: 这里太冷了，我的牙齿都在打颤。

original: If you see one riding a boar, don't laugh. They hate that.
string: 如果看到有人骑着野猪，可别笑。他们可不喜欢别人笑话。

original: I much prefer these quiet places to those inns in cities. It's easier to relax here.
string: 我更喜欢这种宁静的地方，而不是城市里的旅店。在这里更容易放松。

original: Middle of nowhere, one inn, one drunk, one lunatic. Feels... oddly comforting.
string: 偏僻的地方，一家旅店，一个醉汉，一个疯子。感觉......奇怪地让人安心。

original: I wonder if the owner ever considered that people don't come here much because of that orc bard.
string: 不知道店主有没有想过，人们不常来这里，是因为那个兽人吟游诗人吧？

original: You know, I heard something actually happened once in this dull little place.
string: 你知道吗？我听说这个无聊的小地方，其实发生过一件事。

original: There's nothing like a good mug of ale. And yes, what you get in here is nothing like a good mug of ale.
string: 没有什么比一杯好酒更舒服的了。而这里的酒......可称不上是好酒。

original: The bard in here should stick to serving drinks and providing... other services, instead of singing.
string: 这里的吟游诗人还是专心侍酒和提供... 其他服务吧，别老是唱歌。

original: Not a bad little place this. It's basic, but it has enough for the weary traveller.
string: 这个地方还不错。虽然简陋，但对疲惫的旅人来说足够了。

original: Not bad, for a place that probably waters down its ale with snow.
string: 对于一个可能用雪来兑酒的地方来说，这酒还算可以。

original: The owner of this place doesn't like Dunmer. But that's fine with me. I don't like her either.
string: 这家店的老板不喜欢丹莫。不过这很符合我的心意，我也不喜欢她。

original: You know it's not bad in here. Near enough to Solitude, but without all the crowds.
string: 这里还算不错。离独孤很近，但没有那么多闹哄哄的人。

original: The mead's not bad here. Although I suspect that's because nobody lives long enough to complain about it.
string: 这里的蜜酒还行。不过我猜是因为没人活得够久来抱怨它。

original: A warm fire, decent ale and fewer flies than I anticipated. I'll call that a minor victory.
string: 温暖的火炉、还过得去的啤酒，而且苍蝇比我预想的少。这已经算是小胜利了。

original: Argonians. Pfft. I'll never truly forgive them for what they did to Mournhold in the Third Era.
string: 阿尔贡。哼。他们在第三纪元对哀伤城所做的事，我永远不会原谅。

original: I don't like it in here. What does an Argonian know about running an inn?
string: 我不喜欢这里。一个阿尔贡懂什么经营旅店？

original: Ah, the Bard's College. Where would Skyrim be without endless songs about heroes who died doing something stupid?
string: 啊，吟游诗人学院。如果没有无数关于英雄们因做蠢事而死的歌谣，天际会是什么样子？

original: You know, after coming back to Skyrim, I'm starting to miss the simplicity of Solstheim's ash storms.
string: 你知道吗，回到天际之后，我开始怀念索瑟海姆的灰风暴的简单了。

original: My goodness. Even the snow looks tired here.
string: 天啊，就连这里的雪看起来都疲惫不堪。

original: This place has a lot of miners. It's cold and it's full of people who hate their lives. Makes me feel right at home.
string: 这个地方有很多矿工。又冷又充满了厌恶生活的人。让我感到格外亲切。

original: Dawnstar. Cold enough to freeze a netch's arse. And half as welcoming.
string: 晨星。冷得连气母的屁股都能冻僵。而且半点也不热情。

original: You think with all the thieves here, one of them might have stolen some soap. And, you know? Used it?
string: 你觉得这里这么多小偷，或许有人偷了肥皂吧？而且，你知道吗？还用了它？

original: I don't know what's worse here, the stench of corruption, or the smell of fish.
string: 这里更糟糕的不是腐败的气味，而是鱼腥味。

original: Try dropping something on the floor. I dare you.
string: 试试把什么东西扔到地上。我就不信你不敢。

original: If I ever retire, it would probably be to somewhere with walls like this. Preferably with fewer Nords though...
string: 如果我哪天退休，可能会选择像这里一样有城墙的地方。当然，最好少点诺德人......

original: You know, I quite like it here. Plenty of rich fools willing to hire a sell-sword who knows what he's doing.
string: 你知道吗，我还挺喜欢这里的。有很多有钱的傻瓜，愿意雇佣一个知道自己在干什么的佣兵。

original: It's nice here, I'll give you that. But if there's one thing I've learned in all my years, the prettier the city, the uglier the politics.
string: 这里确实不错，我得承认。但多年来我学到的一点是：城市越漂亮，政治越肮脏。

original: Some of the folk here glare at me like I still owe them money. Truth is, I probably do.
string: 这里有些人总是瞪着我，好像我还欠他们钱似的。说实话，我可能确实欠了他们一些。

original: I lived here for a time you know? Didn't much like it. Some of the people were alright though.
string: 我曾在这里住过一段时间，你知道吗？并不喜欢这个地方。不过这里的一些人还算可以。

original: I hope we don't run into that Elda woman. Hateful person. Never anything nice to say about my kind.
string: 我希望我们别遇到那个女人艾尔达。她是个讨厌的人，从来没有对我说过好话。

original: I did some odd jobs for Revyn while I lived here. They were not always strictly, uh, legal?
string: 我曾在这里为瑞温做过一些零工，那些工作并不总是——呃，完全合法？

original: The markets here aren't bad. You can pick up some things from my homeland too.
string: 这里的集市还不错，你还能买到一些我家乡的东西。

original: Rolff Stone-Fist tried his nonsense with me once. He left with a bloody nose and a bruised ego.
string: 罗尔夫·石拳曾经试图和我耍花样，结果鼻子流血，自尊心也受损。

original: You think a city named Whiterun would have more snow, eh? False advertising, I say.
string: 你以为一个叫白漫的城市会有更多的雪吗？我看这纯属虚假宣传。

original: I hope we don't have to go in Belethor's place while we're here. Sleazy little man, I might end up punching him. Again.
string: 我希望我们在这里待的期间，不必去贝莱托尔的地方。那个家伙太龌龊了，我可能又会忍不住揍他一顿。

original: I once had a brief dalliance with one of the women here. Turns out, she was married. She didn't tell me. I didn't ask.
string: 我曾经和这里的一个女人有过一段短暂的风流韵事。结果她已经结婚了，她没告诉我，我也没问。

original: This place is so small, you could sneeze and hit every house in the village.
string: 这个地方太小了，你打个喷嚏都能把村子里的每一间房子都打到。

original: You know, I actually miss Solstheim? I miss the little things. Like Ash Yams. I love Ash Yams.
string: 你知道吗？我其实还挺想念索瑟海姆的？想念那些小事。比如灰烬薯。我特别喜欢灰烬薯。

original: Solstheim had its charm. Mostly hidden. Very hidden.
string: 索瑟海姆有它独特的魅力。不过大多是隐藏着的。非常隐秘。

original: You know, there are collectors who will pay handsomely for Dwemer parts. Provided we get out of here alive.
string: 你知道吗？有收藏家愿意出高价买锻莫部件。当然，前提是我们能活着离开这里。

original: Some say the Heart of Lorkhan powered their greatest machines. If that's true, they were even madder than I thought.
string: 有人说，洛克汗之心为他们最伟大的机械提供动力。如果这是真的，他们比我想象中更疯狂。

original: They listen with their teeth, I swear.
string: 我发誓，它们是用牙齿听声音的。

original: Once mer, now something twisted by darkness. Reminds me to stay in the light.
string: 曾经是精灵，现在却被黑暗扭曲成这样。让我想要待在光明中。

original: I've slept in some foul places, but even I have standards. ... Low ones, apparently.
string: 我睡过不少肮脏的地方，但就连我也有底线......显然，我的底线很低。

original: Dark tunnels and stale air. Wonderful.
string: 阴暗的隧道和闷热的空气。真让人心旷神怡。

original: Takes a certain kind of stubborn to work these depths.
string: 要有特别的执拗才能在这深处工作。

original: Makes you appreciate sunlight, doesn't it?
string: 这让你更加珍惜阳光，不是吗？

original: Seen plenty of tunnels back home. Never liked them much.
string: 在家乡见过不少隧道。从来不太喜欢那些地方。

original: Tough folk, the Orsimer. No use for charm, plenty for axes.
string: 奥辛莫可真够硬气的。他们不讲什么花哨，就知道砍砍杀杀。

original: Try not to offend anyone. They settle arguments with warhammers.
string: 尽量别得罪人。这里的人动不动就用战锤解决争端。

original: Careful how you look at the chief's mate. They take offense quickly, and personally.
string: 别随便盯着酋长的伴侣看。他们动不动就生气，而且记仇。

original: Lovely place for a stroll. Just mind the corpses and splinters.
string: 这里倒是个散步的好地方。就是要小心那些尸体和碎片。

original: Shipwrecks always hide something unpleasant.
string: 船只失事的地方总藏着些不愉快的东西。

original: Let me guess - this shop boasts the best goods and the best prices, just like all the others, eh?
string: 让我猜猜——这家店说不定声称自己货品最好、价格最优，和其他店一样吧？

original: At least it's warm inside. That's worth something.
string: 至少里面暖和点。这点总算值得称道。

original: Don't touch anything fragile. They'll probably expect you to pay for it.
string: 别碰那些易碎的东西。他们可能会让你赔偿。

original: Seen finer work in Morrowind. Seen worse too.
string: 在晨风见过更精致的工艺，也见过更糟的。

original: Bottles everywhere. One wrong step and we owe a fortune.
string: 到处都是酒瓶。一不小心就得赔上一大笔。

original: You can smell the harbor from here. Better than smelling the guests.
string: 从这里能闻到港口的味道。比闻客人们强多了。

original: Plenty of stone to shout at. Nords like their gods loud.
string: 有的是石头可以大喊大叫。诺德人喜欢大声祷告。

original: If the Divines care, they hide it well.
string: 如果神灵在乎，他们可藏得够好。

original: Try not to knock anything over. Holy things tend to explode spectacularly.
string: 别把什么东西碰倒了。圣物爆炸起来可不轻。

original: My last employer had faith enough for ten men. Didn't save him though.
string: 我上一家雇主的信仰够十个人用了。可还是没能救他。

original: Werewolves. Wonderful. My favorite.
string: 狼人？太棒了。我最喜欢的。

original: If we're lucky, they're out hunting. If not... well.
string: 如果运气好，他们出去猎了。要是运气不好......唉。

original: Had a bad encounter once. Don't care to repeat it.
string: 以前遇到过一次，不想再经历了。

original: Try not to shout. These walls don't need help coming down.
string: 别大喊大叫。这些墙可不需要帮忙倒塌。

original: Reminds me of a job I took once. Ended badly. Most of them did.
string: 让我想起我曾经接过的一个活儿。结果很惨。大多数都是这样。

original: A simple grave would be too modest, I suppose.
string: 一座简单的坟墓恐怕太过寒酸了，不是吗？

original: Strange how the wind finds its way into every hall.
string: 风总能找到钻进每个大厅的路。真奇怪。

original: Impressive, in a grim, overcompensating sort of way.
string: 很有气势，不过是那种阴森又过度补偿的气势。

original: Nord ruins age well. Better than most people.
string: 诺德人的废墟保存得真好。比大多数人都长寿。

original: Quiet little place... though the mountain keeps a close watch.
string: 一个安静的小地方......不过山峰在暗中监视着一切。

original: Good man, Wilhelm. Nervous, but good.
string: 威尔海姆是个好人，虽然有点紧张。

original: If Geldis says the drink's good, it is. If he says it is safe... well, that's debatable.
string: 如果吉迪斯说酒好喝，那它确实好喝。如果他说它安全......嗯，那可说不准。

original: Sadri's Sujamma... smooth going down, violent on the way back up.
string: 萨德利的苏贾玛......下去时顺畅，上来时却暴烈无比。

original: Careful with the miners that come here. Stand too close, and they'll tell you exactly how much they hate their shift.
string: 小心这里的矿工。靠得太近，他们会毫不留情地告诉你他们多么讨厌这班次。

original: Plenty of confidence in this place. Talent... varies.
string: 这里充满自信。才能嘛......参差不齐。

original: I respect anyone who can listen to the same tune a hundred times.
string: 能听同一首曲子一百遍的人，我是很敬佩的。

original: If they ask you to sing, I'm waiting outside.
string: 如果他们让你唱歌，我就等在外面。

original: Lot of lumber moving through. Keeps the place alive, I suppose.
string: 这里木材运输频繁，我想这也是维持生计的方式吧。

original: Nice village. Shame Skyrim keeps happening around it.
string: 好一个宁静的村庄。可惜天际总是发生些不该有的事。

original: Every time I come here, it reminds me of my last patron. Still, he died like a true Nord, fighting until his last breath.
string: 每次来这里，都会让我想起我的最后一位委托人。他死得像个真正的诺德人，战斗到最后一口气。

original: We simply must visit The Bannered Mare while we're here. I might even buy you a drink.
string: 我们一定要去悬旗母马坐坐。我甚至可能会请你喝一杯。

original: I hear the Black-Briars run things round here, despite what others might say.
string: 我听说黑棘家族在这里掌权，无论别人怎么说。

original: You know I've heard things about Haelga. Things I might be interested in... exploring?
string: 我听说过关于哈尔嘉的事。或许有些事我会感兴趣......去探索一下？

original: Falmer hear through stone. Or maybe that one was special.
string: 伐莫能透过石头听见声音。或许那个家伙有特别之处。

original: Chaurus spit melts armor. Not my armor, fortunately. Learned that watching someone else... very briefly.
string: 查鲁斯的唾液能融化盔甲。不过幸好不是我的。我是一边看别人被溅到的...一边学到的教训。

original: Never turn your back on a spriggan. Even if it's dead.
string: 绝不要木灵前转过身去。就算它已经死了。

original: Nords don't seem to mind this. I'll never understand it.
string: 诺德人似乎不在乎这些。我永远都无法理解。

original: Nords walk through this like it's nothing. Must be nice.
string: 诺德人走在这些地方就好像什么事都没有一样。真好。

original: Always liked rain... washes the blood off before it dries.
string: 我总是喜欢雨...能在血干之前冲洗掉。

original: Quiet air. I won't complain.
string: 空气很安静。我不会抱怨。

original: My boots are soaked. Lovely.
string: 我的靴子全湿了。真美妙。

original: Ash again. My favorite... not that you asked.
string: 又是灰烬。我最喜欢的...不过你也没问。

original: Breathe shallow. Helps a little.
string: 浅呼吸。能帮点忙。

original: Feels like the air's trying to shove us off the road.
string: 感觉空气好像在把我们推离这条路。

original: Hard to hear trouble coming... hard for them to hear us too.
string: 难以听见即将到来的危险......他们也难以听见我们的存在。

original: Nice color on the leaves. Shame about the rest.
string: 树叶的颜色真好看。可惜其他地方都不怎么样。

original: Never trusted halls this quiet.
string: 从不信任如此寂静的走廊。

original: Ground's too soft. Never trust soft ground.
string: 地面太软了。别信任软绵绵的地面。

original: Haven't seen trees this old in a long time.
string: 很久没见过这么古老的树木了。

original: Old magic lingers here... the dangerous kind.
string: 这里残留着古老的魔法......危险的那种。

original: Takes a stubborn mind to live this high.
string: 要有顽强的意志才能活在这么高的地方。

original: Long climb, just for a few words.
string: 爬这么久，就为了几句话。

original: I've taken jobs in worse places. Learned nothing good.
string: 我去过比这更糟糕的地方办事。但从没学到什么好东西。

original: Feels like the kind of ground where plans go wrong quickly.
string: 这里的地面让人觉得，计划往往会迅速出错。

original: Quiet folk. Haven't heard anyone shout yet.
string: 安静的人。还没听见谁大喊过。

original: Hard work, quiet hands. Could teach half of Skyrim a lesson.
string: 勤奋的双手，安静的生活。能教会天际半数人一课。

original: They'd outwork most mercenaries I know. Sad truth.
string: 他们能比我认识的大多数佣兵干得更多。可悲的现实。

original: Worked for a wizard once. He said the rats were harmless. They weren't rats.
string: 曾为一位法师效力。他说老鼠无害。那些不是老鼠。

original: Hear that? Rats.. hopefully rats.
string: 听见了吗？老鼠......但愿只是老鼠。

original: Every time I wonder how I ended up in this mess, I remember the gold. It's comforting, in a way.
string: 每当我想知道自己为何陷入这般境地，就会想起那金子。在某种程度上，这让人安心。

original: Most won't remember why they're fighting. Happens often.
string: 大多数人不会记得自己为何而战。这种事经常发生。

original: If we run into someone I've "disappointed", just pretend you don't know me. Long story.
string: 如果遇到我「让失望的人」，就假装不认识我。这是个长故事。

original: Old Teldryn will see you right. Give him some gold, he'll join the fight, [humming] uh, alright.
string: 老泰卓因会帮你的。给他些金子，他就会加入战斗。[哼唱声]唔，好吧。

original: Teldryn Sero, the dashing hero... ever daring... ever bold... if of course, he gets some gold.
string: 泰卓因·赛罗，那个英勇的英雄......总是勇敢......总是无畏......当然，只要他有金子。

original: Oh sweet maiden of Hadleyshire...etc. Hehehe... I love that song.
string: 哦，哈德利郡的甜美少女......等等。嘿嘿嘿......我爱这首歌。

original: Women, women, women! Hehehe!
string: 女人，女人，女人！嘿嘿嘿！

original: Give me a maiden, and I'll turn her into a - oh - heh - I thought I was singing that in my head.
string: 给我一个少女，我就把她变成——哦——嘿——我刚才在脑子里唱的歌。

original: The Lusty Argonian maid...hehehe... I met her once... gave her a night she won't forget.
string: 那个元气满满的阿尔贡女仆......嘿嘿嘿......我见过她一次......给了她一个她永生难忘的夜晚。

original: Ladies, or otherwise, do gather round. Old Teldryn will uh - something something something.
string: 女士们，或者其他任何人，都请围过来。老泰卓因会——呃——什么什么什么。

original: I once tried my hand at poetry you know. There once was a man from Riften, who had quite the thing for a chicken. He took it for dinner, and mistook it for the main course. What? I never said it was good poetry?
string: 我曾经试过写诗呢。从前有个裂谷的男人，他对一只鸡情有独钟。他把它当晚餐吃了，还以为这是主菜呢。什么？我可没说这是好诗！

original: (humming)
string: （哼唱）

original: (humming)
string: （哼唱）

original: (humming)
string: （哼唱）

original: (humming)
string: （哼唱）

original: (humming)
string: （哼哼）

original: (humming)
string: （哼哼）

original: I'm itching all over. I think that fish I had the other day was on the turn or something.
string: 我浑身发痒。我怀疑那天吃的那条鱼可能已经变质了。

original: (Belch) Oh dear. Sorry about that.
string: （打嗝）哦天啊，抱歉。

original: Is it just me, or do you have a - uh - never mind. Forget I mentioned it.
string: 是我自己觉得吗？还是你也有——呃——算了，我刚刚说什么呢。

original: Something about this place reminds me of... uh... something I'd rather forget, actually.
string: 这个地方让我想起了......呃......我其实宁愿忘记的东西。

original: I'm quite bored.
string: 我有点无聊。

original: Not much happening, is there?
string: 这里没什么好玩的，是吧？

original: I'm quite tired you know.
string: 我有点累了，你知道吗？

original: Try not to get us killed here. I've just polished my armor.
string: 尽量别让我们在这里送命。我刚把盔甲擦亮呢。

original: You know, if a cliff racer swooped down on us here, I wouldn't be surprised. You just seem to attract bad luck.
string: 你知道吗？如果这里突然冲下一只峭壁行者，我也不会感到惊讶。你总是招惹倒霉事。

original: Remind me again why we're doing this? Actually... never mind. Your coin's answer enough.
string: 再提醒我一次我们为什么要做这件事？算了......算了，你的钱已经是个足够的答案了。

original: If I get disintegrated by some ancient Dwarven contraption, tell people it was heroic, eh?
string: 如果我被什么古代矮人机关给粉碎了，记得告诉别人这是英勇就行。

original: All this fresh air... it's unnatural. Give me ash storms any day.
string: 这么多新鲜空气......真不自然。我宁愿要灰烬风暴。

original: If my ears freeze off, I expect a bonus from you. A large one.
string: 如果我的耳朵冻掉了，我要你给我一大笔补偿。

original: I can't see a thing. If we walk off a cliff, I want it on record that it was your idea.
string: 我什么也看不见。如果我们掉下悬崖，我要记录下来这是你的主意。

original: If you're lost, just pretend you know where we're going. I won't tell.
string: 如果你迷路了，就假装知道去哪儿。我不会说的。

original: Companions... always going on about glory. Passable sellswords, at best
string: 同伴......总是嚷嚷什么荣耀。最多也就是些合格的佣兵罢了。

original: We should be quiet in here. No telling what might be lurking. You know? In the dark?
string: 这里我们应该保持安静。不知道黑暗中会有什么东西潜伏着。懂我的意思吗？

original: Sometimes you know - stealth is the better option. Like now, for example?
string: 有时候你知道——潜行才是更好的选择。比如现在这种情况？

original: All this sneaking around? Is it really necessary?
string: 这么鬼鬼祟祟的，真的有必要吗？

original: You know, I was just... oh sorry. Was that too loud?
string: 你知道吗，我刚才只是......哦，抱歉。声音太大了吗？

original: All this creeping around is hurting my back you know.
string: 这鬼鬼祟祟的动作把我的背都弄疼了。

original: Nothing quite like sneaking up on a bandit and slitting their throat - eh?
string: 没什么比偷袭一名强盗，然后割断他的喉咙更爽快的了——对吧？

original: We should be quiet in here. Not that I'm afraid, mind. Just being... respectful.
string: 这里我们应该保持安静。又不是我胆小。只是......出于尊重。

original: Good idea, let's stay quiet. Draugr have sharp hearing.
string: 说得对，我们保持安静吧。尸鬼的听觉非常敏锐。

original: You do know Falmer can't see anything, right?
string: 你可知道伐莫什么都看不见，对吧？

original: There's death in these walls. Old, angry death.
string: 这些墙壁里充满了死亡的气息，古老而充满怨恨。

original: Sneaking up on a giant never ends well. Get ready to run for it.
string: 偷袭巨人可不会有好结果。做好准备，赶紧逃命吧。

original: Keep quiet. They hear too well.
string: 保持安静。他们听觉太敏锐了。

original: Why are we sneaking? Engaging in a bit of shoplifting, are we?
string: 我们为什么要偷偷摸摸的？是想来点小偷小摸吗？

original: Oh, are we trying to sneak out without paying?
string: 哦，我们是想溜走而不付钱吗？

original: No point trying to hide in here. The gods see all. Apparently.
string: 藏在这里也没用。众神无所不见。显然如此。

original: You trying to hide from the guards? Have you been naughty?
string: 你是想躲避卫兵吗？你是否做了什么不该做的事？

original: What? Me? Lady, I'm neither gallant, nor a hero.
string: 什么？我？女士，我既不是英雄，也不是骑士。

original: Wait, are you talking to me? I've heard it all now.
string: 等等，你是在和我说话吗？我什么都听过了。

original: Well I don't really do romance dear. Not since... ah, never mind.
string: 亲爱的，我可不擅长浪漫。自从......算了，不提也罢。

original: Oh, I'm sure you'll get over it. One day.
string: 哦，我确信你总会好起来的。总有一天。

original: Don't worry about it. I get it a lot.
string: 别担心。我经常听到这种事。

original: Keep asking dear. I'm sure someone will take you up on it. Eventually.
string: 继续问吧，亲爱的。总会有人接受你的邀请。迟早的。

original: Disappointing.
string: 真失望。

original: That's really a shame.
string: 这确实很遗憾。

original: Oh. Well, that's... awkward. Sorry to have brought it up.
string: 哦。嗯，那是挺……尴尬的。抱歉了。

original: Oh. I'm sorry I said anything, then.
string: 哦，很抱歉我说了那些话。

original: Oh hello!
string: 哦，你好！

original: Are you my gallant hero? Have you come to whisk me away, to a life of adventure and romance?
string: 你是我那勇敢的英雄吗？你是来带我离开这里，过上充满冒险和浪漫的生活的吗？

original: Oh you know me. I always land on my feet.
string: 哦，你认识我。我总是能落地站稳。

original: Been worse. But... been better too.
string: 也曾更糟......但也曾更好。

original: Not bad, but I don't miss this place.
string: 还不错，但我不想念这个地方。

original: Farewell.
string: 再会。

original: Yes, bye.
string: 是的，再见。

original: Was almost good to see you.
string: 差点还挺想见你。

original: See you again, no doubt.
string: 我们还会再见面，毫无疑问。

original: Decent enough fellow that.
string: 这个人还算可以。

original: He's not bad. Tolerable at least.
string: 他还行。至少还能忍受。

original: Nice to see not everyone in Windhelm hates me.
string: 看来并非这里的每个人都讨厌我。

original: You know, if I didn't know better, I'd say she has a little crush on me.
string: 你知道吗？如果我猜得没错，她可能有点喜欢我呢。

original: I think she's still mad at me for some reason. But a gentleman never kisses and tells, eh?
string: 我猜她还是在为某事生我的气。不过，绅士从不道出吻过谁，对吧？

original: Oh, a bit of this... and a bit of that. You know me.
string: 哦，这个嘛......有点这个，有点那个。你了解我。

original: Well, I... uh... wanted to see you... of course. Hehe.
string: 呃......我就是想见见你......当然啦。嘿嘿。

original: I was just passing through really, thought I'd pop by and see how things are.
string: 我只是路过，顺便来看看近况罢了。

original: She's so grumpy isn't she?
string: 她不是很爱发脾气吗？

original: These Windhelm women eh? So cool in public. But in private? Well... that would be telling.
string: 这些风舵的女人啊？在公众面前那么冷静。可私底下呢？......那可就难说了。

original: I think she's still mad at me for some reason. But a gentleman never kisses and tells, eh?
string: 我猜她还是在为某事生我的气。不过，绅士从不道出吻过谁，对吧？

original: Oh come on! You're still mad with me?
string: 别装了！你还在生我的气吗？

original: I just came to annoy you.
string: 我只是来烦你的。

original: You Nords just don't forget do you? One tiny disagreement and you bear a grudge for life.
string: 你们诺德人就是不会忘事是吧？一点小小的不合就要记恨一辈子。

original: I'm not here by choice, believe me.
string: 我可不是自愿来的，相信我。

original: Always such a warm welcome from you eh?
string: 你总是这么热情地欢迎我是吧？

original: I'm going.
string: 我要走了。

original: So sorry to have bothered you.
string: 很抱歉打扰你了。

original: I'll leave when I'm ready.
string: 我走的时候自己会决定。

original: Hehehe.
string: 嘿嘿嘿。

original: What an idiot, eh?
string: 真个蠢货是吧？

original: Got nothing between his ears, that one.
string: 那家伙脑子里空空如也。

original: You know, he's one of the reasons I hated living in Windhelm.
string: 你知道吗，他是我讨厌在风舵生活的原因之一。

original: Do we have to stay here?
string: 我们非得待在这里吗？

original: Cold stiffens bodies. Makes dragging them harder.
string: 寒冷会使身体僵硬，拖动起来更费劲。

original: Snow keeps sound down. Handy, if you're careful.
string: 雪能压低声音。如果小心点的话，这很有用。

original: Big place. Lots of places to die in.
string: 地方很大，有很多地方可以送命。

original: Nords and their grand entrances... shame about the company.
string: 诺德人总是喜欢大张旗鼓地进场......可惜陪伴的人选。

original: Got em!
string: 抓住他了！

original: No, me either.
string: 不，我也不喜欢。

original: Yes, I quite agree.
string: 是的，我完全同意。

original: I can see why you'd say that.
string: 我也能理解你这么说。

original: Nope, not interested.
string: 不，我没兴趣。

original: Oh, do be quiet.
string: 哦，别吵了。

original: Do you ever shut up?
string: 你就不能闭嘴吗？

original: Miraak, is it? Can't say I like the sound of him. Anyone with fanatics that eager to stab you is usually bad news.
string: 米拉克？听起来不太好。凡是有那么热切想杀了你的狂热分子，通常都不是什么好人。

original: You ever notice how people with temples always think they're gods? Never ends well.
string: 你有没有发现，那些有神庙的人总爱自称是神？结果从来都好不到哪儿去。

original: Cozy place. Needs a little light, a little less death magic.
string: 这里挺温馨的。就是有点暗，还有点死气沉沉。

original: Your new friend seems competent. That's... something.
string: 你的新朋友看起来还挺有能力的。这......算是个好事吧。

original: Dark corridors, foul air... real hospitality. Aren't we lucky?
string: 黑漆漆的走廊，空气恶臭......真够热情好客的。我们可真走运。

original: So, this Miraak hides, yet demands shrines and sacrifice. Modest fellow indeed.
string: 米拉克藏起来还要人祭祀？这家伙还真谦虚。

original: A book locked away in a cursed temple. By all means, open it. What could go wrong?
string: 一本被锁在诅咒寺庙里的书。当然，你就打开它吧。能有什么问题呢？

original: The Skaal, hm? A village of stubborn Nords living on frozen land. Sounds tempting.
string: 斯卡尔村？一个顽固的诺德人村落，坐落在冰封的土地上。听起来很有吸引力。

original: Dragons leave their words everywhere. Shame they don't leave coin.
string: 龙在处处留下它们的文字。可惜它们不留下金币。

original: Controlling a stone with your voice... I've seen stranger things. Not many.
string: 仅凭吼声就能操控石头......我见过更奇怪的事。但不多。

original: The Skaal may thank you, but don't expect a feast. They strike me as the stoic sort.
string: 斯卡尔人或许会感谢你，但别指望有盛宴。他们看起来是那种冷静寡言的族群。

original: If anyone knows about cursed books, it's a Telvanni. Of course it is.
string: 如果有人懂得诅咒之书，那一定是泰瓦尼。当然了。

original: Neloth is the type who'd burn down a city just to warm his tea.
string: 内洛斯就是那种为了给茶水加热，连整座城都能烧个精光的家伙。

original: Telvanni power runs deep. I'd rather have him as an ally than an enemy...
string: 泰瓦尼力量根深蒂固。我宁愿他成为盟友而非敌人......

original: Ancient, flooded, and full of things that want us dead. Homey, isn't it?
string: 古老、被淹没，且充满想要置我们于死地的东西。真让人向往，不是吗？

original: I'd wager Neloth values these machines more than the lives of anyone here.
string: 我猜内洛斯会比这里任何人的性命更看重这些机器。

original: Lovely ruin. Almost makes me miss bandits.
string: 美丽的废墟。差点让我怀念强盗了。

original: Neloth, Miraak, Hermaeus Mora... seems we've gathered the worst company possible.
string: 内洛斯、米拉克、赫麦尤斯·莫拉......看来我们聚集了最糟糕的同伴。

original: So the old shaman gives his life, and you get the Word. Fair trade? I'll let you decide.
string: 老萨满献出性命，你却得到了文字。公平交易吗？我让你自己判断。

original: I've walked behind many who didn't return. Try not to join them.
string: 我曾跟随许多人，他们却再也没有回来。希望你别加入他们。

original: Ash spawn. As if Solstheim wasn't miserable enough.
string: 灰烬怪。好像索瑟海姆还不够悲惨一样。

original: Fort Frostmoth. The Imperials left it to rot after Red Mountain. Seems it found new tenants.
string: 霜蛾堡。红山之后，帝国人任其荒废。看来它找到了新的主人。

original: Seen forts like this before. Always full of ghosts. Sometimes the living kind.
string: 见过这样的堡垒。总是充斥着鬼魂。有时还有活人。

original: You can almost hear soldiers marching. Habit of the dead, I suppose.
string: 你几乎能听到士兵行军的声音。我想，这是死者的习惯吧。

original: So, the ash spawn are gone. Give Raven Rock a week before something else goes wrong.
string: 灰烬怪已经离开了。给鸦石镇一个星期，然后再等着看什么事会出错。

original: If a Redoran councillor needs outsiders, things must be worse than they're saying.
string: 如果瑞多然的议员需要外人帮忙，那么情况一定比传闻的更糟。

original: Nothing good ever starts with offerings in a tomb.
string: 任何好事都不会从坟墓中的祭品开始。

original: Strange family, too quiet. Always a sign someone's hiding a blade.
string: 奇怪的家庭，太安静了。总是有人藏着刀的征兆。

original: Morag Tong... that's no common rabble. Someone paid dearly for this.
string: 莫拉格堂......这可不是普通的乌合之众。有人为此付出了昂贵的代价。

original: A manor in Raven Rock. That's a step up from sleeping in the ash.
string: 位于鸦石镇的庄园。比在灰烬中过夜强多了。

original: A missing smith. Skaal don't lose people easily, something's off.
string: 失踪的铁匠。斯卡尔人不会轻易失去人，这里有蹊跷。

original: Trust the Thalmor to chain a man rather than bargain with him.
string: 还是信任梭默吧，他们宁愿用锁链束缚人，也不愿与人谈判。

original: Baldor's lucky he was only tied up. The Thalmor don't often show restraint.
string: 鲍德尔运气还不错，只是被绑住了。梭默可不常手下留情。

original: So the Thalmor want to own Stalhrim now. Surprised it took them this long.
string: 原来梭默想要占有魔冰。真让人惊讶他们花了这么久。

original: For all their pride, they die like everyone else. Just noisier.
string: 尽管他们自命不凡，但死起来和别人一样。只是更吵闹罢了。

original: Not the worst tomb I've walked into. Grim enough, though.
string: 还算不上我进过的最糟糕的坟墓。不过也够阴森的。

original: With scholars, it's never just a ruin. It's always something more... inconvenient.
string: 对于学者来说，这从来不是简单的废墟。总是有更多......让人头疼的东西。

original: Last time I worked with a historian, the "discovery" nearly buried us.
string: 上次和历史学家合作，那所谓的「发现」差点要了我们的命。

original: Nord history tends to shout. Tradition, I suppose.
string: 诺德人的历史总是大声宣告。传统吧，我想。

original: Someone took their watch seriously.
string: 有人把守卫的职责当真了。

original: Imagine holding your duty that long... makes my old contracts look easy.
string: 想象一下，一个人能把职责坚持那么久......让我那些老契约看起来都轻松了。

original: Of all the Dragon Priests to meet, we find the dutiful one.
string: 所有遇到的龙祭司中，偏偏遇上这个尽责的。

original: So that's what we're doing now? Errands for The Companions?
string: 这就是我们现在要做的事？给战友团跑腿？

original: More searching dungeons for old junk. How thrilling.
string: 又是去挖掘古墓寻找破烂。多刺激。

original: Meeting people in the dark often doesn't end well you know?
string: 在黑暗中见人，往往不会有好结果，你知道吗？

original: I don't like funerals, but I guess we should go.
string: 我不喜欢葬礼，但看来我们还是得去。

original: I've got a bad feeling about this place...
string: 我对这个地方有不好的预感......

original: How much are you getting paid for this tedious task?
string: 这单无聊的差事你拿多少报酬？

original: Oh I love killing bandits. I'd have taken this job for free.
string: 哦，我最喜欢杀死强盗了。这活儿我都愿意免费干。

original: Remember, vampires don't even have to touch you to infect you.
string: 记住，吸血鬼甚至不需要碰你就能传染你。

original: All right, old guardian. Let's see why they feared you.
string: 好啦，老守卫。让我看看他们为什么害怕你。

original: And out of the shadows comes... that. I hate being right.
string: 而从阴影中出现的......是它。我讨厌自己说得对。

original: Well if it isn't Teldryn Sero, back in Windhelm.
string: 哟，原来是泰卓因·赛罗，你又回风舵来了。

original: Hey Sero, you old sell-sword!
string: 嘿，赛罗，你这老佣兵！

original: Oh look, it's Teldryn. A legend in his own mind.
string: 哦，看看是谁，泰卓因。自封的传奇人物。

original: Didn't think you'd show your face here again, you know, after the 'incident'?
string: 没想到你还会再出现在这里，要知道，那次‘事件’之后。

original: Oh look who it is. I thought you'd be ashamed to come back here.
string: 哦，原来是你。我还以为你会羞于再回来呢。

original: By the Gods! Teldryn! Is that really you? What a nerve!
string: 众神在上！泰卓因！真的是你吗？你还真敢！

original: Teldryn Sero? Wow, is that really you?
string: 泰卓因·赛罗？哇，真的是你？

original: Well well, if it isn't my least favorite Dunmer mercenary.
string: 哟哟，原来是我最不喜欢的丹莫佣兵。

original: (whistles) Wow. You're back. Looks like I won that bet eh?
string: （吹口哨） 哇，你还活着。看来我赢了那场赌注吧？

original: Teldryn Sero? Really? You've got some nerve.
string: 泰卓因·赛罗？真的？你还真有脸！

original: I'm pretty sure you still owe me money from that card game.
string: 我记得你还欠我那场牌局的钱呢。

original: Isn't there still a bounty on you?
string: 你身上不是还有悬赏令吗？

original: Don't you still have an outstanding fine here in the hold?
string: 你不是还欠着领地里的罚款吗？

original: I think you broke my colleague's heart you know.
string: 我听说你还伤了我同事的心呢。

original: I'm disappointed in you. Was it all just a one night thing for you?
string: 我对你很失望。这不过是你的一夜风流吗？

original: Don't think I've forgotten about what you did you know? My knees are still sore.
string: 别以为我忘了你干的那些事儿？我的膝盖到现在还疼着呢。

original: So you're back. Did you remember what you promised me?
string: 你又回来了？你还记得你答应我的事吗？

original: You've got a nerve coming back here. Did you at least get it cleaned after what you did to it?
string: 你还好意思回来？你把那地方弄成那样，至少收拾干净了吧？

original: I heard what you did you know? Is it true?
string: 我听说你干的那些事儿了？是真的吗？

original: There's a rumour going round about you. I can't even bring myself to say it out loud. Surely it can't really have happened?
string: 关于你的传言满天飞，我连说出口都不敢。真的会发生那种事吗？

original: Someone told me what you did. And in a temple of all places. Tell me, is that what really happened?
string: 有人告诉我你干的那些事儿。而且还是在神殿里。告诉我，那都是真的吗？

original: Every time I see you, I think about that time you got caught with that thing, you know, in that place?
string: 每次看到你，我就想起你被抓住时的事——你记得那件事，还有那个地方？

original: Aren't you still a suspect for those robberies that happened here?
string: 你还不是那些抢劫案的嫌疑人吗？

original: Yeah, deny it all you want, but we guards remember things.
string: 随便你怎么否认，但我们守卫可不会忘事。

original: Just behave yourself here in Windhelm or we're going to have a problem.
string: 在风舵里给我老实点，否则我们可就麻烦大了。

original: Just remember, we can lock you up. Again.
string: 记住，我们可以再次把你关起来。

original: Don't cross me Dunmer, or else...
string: 别惹我，丹莫，否则...

original: Just behave yourself, I won't think twice about throwing you in jail.
string: 乖乖待着，我可不会犹豫把你关进监狱。

original: Well, whatever you're doing here, get it done and get out of Windhelm.
string: 不管怎么说，你在这里做什么，快做完就滚出风舵。

original: I don't believe a word that comes out of your mouth!
string: 我才不信你嘴里说的话呢！

original: You know what, I don't want to hear your excuses. Just know, I'm watching you.
string: 算了，我不想听你的借口。记住，我在盯着你。

original: Keep your nose clean in my city, otherwise... you know?
string: 在我的城市里别惹事，否则... 你懂的。

original: I hate mercenaries and I hate Dunmer, so best just stay out of my way eh?
string: 我讨厌佣兵，也讨厌丹莫，所以最好别惹我。

original: What do you want, guard?
string: 你想干什么，卫兵？

original: The one and only, yes.
string: 就是我本人，没错。

original: Oh I was hoping to avoid all this silliness.
string: 哦，我还指望能避开这些无聊的事呢。

original: Oh, here we go again. What?
string: 哦，又来了。什么事？

original: Oh great, another judgmental guard.
string: 哦，又是个爱评头品足的卫兵。

original: Come on then, let's get this over with shall we?
string: 来吧，那我们快点把这事了结算了。

original: That's me. Master swordsman at your ser- oh - it's you. What do you want?
string: 是我啊。大剑师在您的服务中——哦，是你。你想要什么？

original: Er - no?
string: 呃——不？

original: No, of course not. It's not true.
string: 不，当然不是。这不是真的。

original: I think you'll find you're mistaken.
string: 我想你应该是弄错了。

original: No, no, that's not the case at all.
string: 不，不，情况完全不是这样。

original: I - uh - have no recollection of that.
string: 我——呃——完全不记得这事了。

original: Surely you're mistaking me for another dashing swordsman?
string: 你一定是把我当成别的风度翩翩的剑客了吧？

original: I have no idea what you're going on about.
string: 我完全不知道你在说什么。

original: Hehe! Really? Got any proof that it was actually me?
string: 嘿嘿！真的吗？有什么证据证明那件事是我干的？

original: Oh come now. There's really no need to dredge up the past, is there?
string: 哦，算了吧。真的没必要翻旧账吧？

original: Oh come on woman, you're still going on about that?
string: 哦，拜托，你还在说那件事啊？

original: Oh come on man. Really? That was years ago.
string: 哦，拜托，那都是多年前的事了。

original: Well... that was awkward.
string: 呃......这个场面有点尴尬。

original: These guards eh?
string: 这些卫兵是吧？

original: That fellow is such an idiot. Always got something to say.
string: 那个家伙真够蠢的，总是爱多嘴。

original: I certainly don't miss Windhelm, this reminds me why.
string: 我可不想念风舵，这让我想起为什么。

original: Windhelm guards. You'd think I was some kind of monster, the way they treat me.
string: 风舵卫兵。他们看我的眼神，我还以为自己是什么怪物呢。

original: You know he's probably right, but I'm admitting nothing.
string: 我知道他可能是对的，但我什么都不承认。

original: You know she's probably right, but I'm admitting nothing.
string: 我知道她可能是对的，但我什么都不承认。

original: I've said it before and I'll say it again. I kill bandits for free.
string: 我之前说过，我也会再重复一遍：我免费杀强盗。

original: Hold on to your weapons. Some of these Draugr can shout them out of your very hands.
string: 紧握你的武器。这里的一些尸鬼甚至能从你手中夺走武器。

original: If the Draugr don't kill us, chances are the dust probably will.
string: 如果尸鬼杀不了我们，那么很可能就是尘埃会要了我们的命。

original: Let's be careful not to join the dead here, eh?
string: 我们可别在这里加入亡灵的行列，对吧？

original: This place has a dark energy about it. Stay alert.
string: 这个地方充满了阴森的能量。保持警惕。

original: Who knows what we'll find lurking here. Be watchful.
string: 谁知道这里会潜伏着什么。要小心观察。

original: These kind of places are usually full of decent loot.
string: 这种地方通常有不少值钱的战利品。

original: You should consider picking up some Dwemer artefacts here. Might fetch a decent price.
string: 你应该考虑在这里捡一些德沃梅尔文物。或许能卖个好价钱。

original: If you're short on soul gems, be sure to check the machines we manage to kill here.
string: 如果你缺灵魂石，一定要检查我们杀死的机械身上。

original: Oh, I hope we don't run into more puzzles. I hate puzzles.
string: 但愿我们别再遇到更多的谜题。我讨厌谜题。

original: Where you find Falmer you often find Chaurus. Their spit can be deadly.
string: 发现伐莫的地方通常也有查鲁斯。它们的唾液可致命。

original: If you see a Shaman, be sure to target them first.
string: 如果看到萨满，一定要优先攻击他们。

original: Watch the holes in the walls. Falmer can drop right on our heads.
string: 注意墙上的洞。伐莫可能会突然从上面掉下来。

original: Time to kill more savages then, eh?
string: 看来又要杀更多野蛮人了，是吧？

original: Watch out for Briarhearts, they fight like demons.
string: 小心荆棘之心，他们战斗起来像恶魔一样。

original: I wonder if we'll see any of those half-naked women here?
string: 不知道这里会不会有那些半裸的女人？

original: Don't give these filthy bloodsuckers a chance.
string: 别给这些肮脏的吸血鬼任何机会。

original: When we leave this place, let's make sure every vampire is dead, shall we?
string: 离开这里时，我们要确保每一个吸血鬼都死绝，对吧？

original: Let's not leave any survivors here, eh?
string: 这里不能留下任何幸存者，是吧？

original: If you hear howling, get ready to fight.
string: 如果听到狼嚎声，做好战斗准备。

original: Yuck. I can smell the wet, matted fur already.
string: 恶心。我已经闻到那潮湿、乱糟糟的毛发味了。

original: Here we go!
string: 来吧！

original: We've got trouble!
string: 我们有麻烦了！

original: Stay alert!
string: 保持警戒！

original: Come on!
string: 快点！

original: More Draugr, watch out!
string: 更多尸鬼！小心！

original: Oh nice, more bandits to kill!
string: 哇，又有强盗可以杀了！

original: Watch out, bandits!
string: 小心，强盗！

original: Careful, these big cats move quickly.
string: 当心，这些大猫动作很快。

original: More vampires, kill them!
string: 更多吸血鬼，杀了它们！

original: More wolves. They're everywhere.
string: 更多狼了，到处都是。

original: Don't let the giant hit you with a club. Trust me, I know.
string: 别让巨人用棍子砸你。相信我，我懂。

original: You don't want to mess about with mammoths. They're tough buggers.
string: 别惹猛犸，它们可不是好惹的。

original: Oh look. A troll.
string: 哦，看，一个巨魔。

original: Watch out for the bear!
string: 小心那只熊！

original: Another bag of bones to kill!
string: 又是一堆骨头要杀！

original: More Ash Spawn! How tiresome.
string: 更多灰烬怪！真让人厌烦。

original: Reavers! Kill them all!
string: 抢匪！全部杀光！

original: Kill the reaver scum!
string: 杀了这些抢匪杂种！

original: Oh come on, more Skeevers? Really?
string: 哦，又是恶鼠？真的吗？

original: Dragon Priest! Don't stand still, they'll get you easily!
string: 龙祭司！别站着不动，他们很容易就能击倒你！

original: Oh great, a dragon, just what we need!
string: 哦，又是一条龙，这正是我们所需要的！

original: Watch out for the archer!
string: 小心那个弓箭手！

original: Keep your head down, there's an archer.
string: 低下头，那边有个弓箭手。

original: Watch that Orc with the greatsword, he can cleave you in two with that!
string: 注意那个手持大剑的兽人，他一剑就能劈你成两半！

original: You summoned 'that'? Next time, maybe something that doesn't tower over castles.
string: 你召唤的是‘那个’吗？下次或许召唤点不会压倒城堡的东西吧。

original: Between the wolves, the weather and the threats in the south, even a simple task like gathering wood for the fire can turn deadly in an instant.
string: 除了狼群、天气还有南边儿来的威胁，即使是像收集柴火这样的小事儿也可能让人突然离世。

original: I do not like this place.
string: 我不喜欢这个地方。

original: I know it is not my place, but... may I offer a word of advice... of warning?
string: 我知道没有这个资格，但是……我能给个建议……或者劝告吗？

original: We Skaal do not fear death.
string: 我们斯卡尔人不惧怕死亡。

original: Well, deadly for you maybe, but not for the greatest swordsman in Morrowind.
string: 好吧，或许对你来说很致命，但对晨风最伟大的剑客来说可不是这样。

original: What, the mighty Frea is afraid of wolves? Aww...
string: 什么，强大的芙瑞雅害怕狼？哎呀......

original: The weather? You're supposed to be tough, aren't you?
string: 天气？你不是很强吗？

original: No, but you're afraid of wolves, and the weather?
string: 不，但你害怕狼，还有天气？

original: Sometimes I think death would be a blessing.
string: 有时候我真想死能是一种恩典。

original: Find anything useful on that corpse?
string: 在尸体上找到什么有用的东西了吗？

original: Don't forget to share any gold you find on them.
string: 别忘了把从他们身上搜到的金子分给我。
